WEBVTT

00:00:03.520 --> 00:00:05.155 line:90% position:50% align:center
Welcome!

00:00:05.155 --> 00:00:09.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here’s a preview of what we’ll discover
in this month’s program.

00:00:10.393 --> 00:00:13.129 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you ever wanted to turn back time

00:00:13.129 --> 00:00:15.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
and undo something
you wish you hadn’t done?

00:00:15.932 --> 00:00:17.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this month’s <i>My Teen Life,</i>

00:00:17.934 --> 00:00:21.671 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’ll hear how Thalila and José,

00:00:21.671 --> 00:00:24.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
who each with help
from their parents and Jehovah,

00:00:24.441 --> 00:00:27.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
made progress after a setback.

00:00:27.977 --> 00:00:30.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we’ve strayed far from Jehovah,

00:00:30.513 --> 00:00:32.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
our own heart may make us feel

00:00:32.582 --> 00:00:34.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
like we could never come back.

00:00:34.984 --> 00:00:36.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
This month’s music video

00:00:36.653 --> 00:00:38.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
will remind us how great

00:00:38.888 --> 00:00:43.493 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah’s love is
for those who want to return to him.

00:00:43.493 --> 00:00:47.664 line:90% position:50% align:center
If a brother once served as an elder
but is not presently,

00:00:47.664 --> 00:00:50.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
what can help him to regain his privileges?

00:00:50.834 --> 00:00:53.470 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll hear the experiences of two brothers

00:00:53.470 --> 00:00:56.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a segment
with this thought-provoking title: 

00:00:56.272 --> 00:00:59.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>Return and Serve Again! </i>

00:00:59.442 --> 00:01:01.711 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s much to look forward to

00:01:01.711 --> 00:01:06.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
in this March 2023 edition
of JW Broadcasting®.

00:01:25.135 --> 00:01:27.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you ever set a goal for yourself

00:01:27.771 --> 00:01:31.174 line:90% position:50% align:center
that was harder to reach
than you first thought?

00:01:32.642 --> 00:01:35.345 line:90% position:50% align:center
How did that make you feel?

00:01:35.345 --> 00:01:37.347 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this dramatization,

00:01:37.347 --> 00:01:41.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
note the adjustments a sister makes
to work toward her goal.

00:01:45.588 --> 00:01:46.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was terrible.

00:01:46.923 --> 00:01:48.992 line:90% position:50% align:center
I could’ve answered that better.

00:01:48.992 --> 00:01:52.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, you did great, really.

00:01:53.663 --> 00:01:55.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ve always been hard on myself.

00:01:56.366 --> 00:01:57.700 line:90% position:50% align:center
... strengthen our faith.

00:01:57.700 --> 00:01:59.769 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then if we,

00:02:00.737 --> 00:02:03.640 line:90% position:50% align:center
um, um—

00:02:06.176 --> 00:02:08.211 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, that’s all.

00:02:09.179 --> 00:02:12.382 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sometimes it made me so anxious

00:02:14.951 --> 00:02:17.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
that even the normal stuff I did

00:02:19.122 --> 00:02:21.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
felt impossible.

00:02:32.202 --> 00:02:35.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what do you think brings this on?

00:02:36.172 --> 00:02:37.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t know, maybe—

00:02:40.143 --> 00:02:44.013 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe lately it’s
because I’m thinking about SKE.

00:02:45.582 --> 00:02:47.917 line:90% position:50% align:center
If I can reach that goal, it’ll be fine.

00:02:49.586 --> 00:02:50.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
I see.

00:02:50.854 --> 00:02:53.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
How about we read
a scripture that might help?

00:02:54.924 --> 00:02:55.992 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:02:56.993 --> 00:02:59.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
They didn’t discourage me from SKE.

00:02:59.762 --> 00:03:03.199 line:90% position:50% align:center
But they suggested
that I try to manage the anxiety first.

00:03:05.301 --> 00:03:07.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
I was on it!

00:03:08.872 --> 00:03:11.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
If I focused on my goal

00:03:20.383 --> 00:03:24.387 line:90% position:50% align:center
and took care of myself, I’d get there.

00:03:32.495 --> 00:03:35.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe it was a little too much focus.

00:03:46.809 --> 00:03:48.811 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you, brothers.

00:03:56.085 --> 00:03:57.120 line:90% position:50% align:center
So?

00:03:58.655 --> 00:03:59.789 line:90% position:50% align:center
They’re right.

00:03:59.789 --> 00:04:01.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
SKE would be a lot for me right now.

00:04:02.225 --> 00:04:03.226 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mm.

00:04:03.960 --> 00:04:08.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m sorry, but you’ll get there.

00:04:10.466 --> 00:04:12.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
I tried everything to fix this.

00:04:12.502 --> 00:04:13.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
What’s wrong with me?

00:04:13.937 --> 00:04:15.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
Nothing.

00:04:15.705 --> 00:04:17.807 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some things just take time.

00:04:19.242 --> 00:04:20.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:04:21.511 --> 00:04:24.747 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hey, I have Lilly’s study tomorrow morning.

00:04:24.747 --> 00:04:26.749 line:90% position:50% align:center
I could use your help.

00:04:27.650 --> 00:04:28.685 line:90% position:50% align:center
OK.

00:04:31.854 --> 00:04:33.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
I want to get baptized,

00:04:34.891 --> 00:04:37.827 line:90% position:50% align:center
but I don’t know.

00:04:38.761 --> 00:04:40.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
You all do so much.

00:04:43.933 --> 00:04:46.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
I don’t think I could ever really be . . .

00:04:54.210 --> 00:04:56.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think I understand.

00:04:56.279 --> 00:04:58.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can I show you something?

00:04:58.481 --> 00:04:59.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
Micah 6:8

00:05:02.819 --> 00:05:04.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
—would you read that?

00:05:06.990 --> 00:05:09.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He has told you, O man, what is good.

00:05:09.959 --> 00:05:12.562 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And what is
Jehovah requiring of you?

00:05:12.562 --> 00:05:16.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Only to exercise justice,
to cherish loyalty,

00:05:16.332 --> 00:05:19.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to walk in modesty with your God!”

00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:23.706 line:90% position:50% align:center
That last part, “walk in modesty,”

00:05:23.706 --> 00:05:27.477 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s about knowing our limitations.

00:05:28.544 --> 00:05:30.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
So is Jehovah happy

00:05:31.581 --> 00:05:33.816 line:90% position:50% align:center
with what you can do,

00:05:33.816 --> 00:05:36.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
or does he want what you can’t do?

00:05:36.919 --> 00:05:39.022 line:90% position:50% align:center
He only expects what I can do.

00:05:41.758 --> 00:05:46.029 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then why should we expect more?

00:05:46.029 --> 00:05:50.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
It turns out I gave Lilly
the same advice the brothers gave me.

00:05:50.767 --> 00:05:52.769 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was my turn to apply it.

00:05:54.871 --> 00:05:57.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had to be honest with myself.

00:05:57.573 --> 00:06:02.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
My limitation was my own high expectation.

00:06:02.278 --> 00:06:06.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’d been doing it so long
that there was no quick fix.

00:06:08.117 --> 00:06:10.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
It didn’t mean giving up on my goals, though.

00:06:14.690 --> 00:06:18.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
I just tried to focus more
on what I could do in the present,

00:06:21.431 --> 00:06:24.734 line:90% position:50% align:center
like having more empathy
for people who feel like I do

00:06:27.537 --> 00:06:30.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
and showing them
how much Jehovah values them.

00:06:35.278 --> 00:06:39.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
We could tell a Bible student how we, um,

00:06:40.950 --> 00:06:42.985 line:90% position:50% align:center
how we overcame a challenge.

00:06:42.985 --> 00:06:43.986 line:90% position:50% align:center
That might . . .

00:06:43.986 --> 00:06:47.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
The truth is,
I can actually do a lot for Jehovah

00:06:50.159 --> 00:06:53.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
with reasonable expectations.

00:06:56.866 --> 00:06:59.602 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our sister learned to manage her anxiety,

00:06:59.602 --> 00:07:03.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
in part,
by managing her expectations

00:07:03.840 --> 00:07:07.443 line:90% position:50% align:center
—a crucial step
to giving her best to Jehovah.

00:07:08.845 --> 00:07:13.282 line:90% position:50% align:center
That lesson is an excellent introduction
to this month’s theme:

00:07:13.282 --> 00:07:15.751 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Realistic Expectations

00:07:15.751 --> 00:07:19.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
—The Key to Joyful and Successful Service.”

00:07:21.390 --> 00:07:24.060 line:10% position:50% align:center
When you hear the word “realistic,”

00:07:24.060 --> 00:07:26.062 line:10% position:50% align:center
what comes to your mind?

00:07:27.230 --> 00:07:30.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Realistic” conveys the idea
of something that is practical,

00:07:30.666 --> 00:07:33.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
rational, reasonable, and sensible.

00:07:35.171 --> 00:07:37.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
Having expectations that are realistic

00:07:37.874 --> 00:07:42.145 line:90% position:50% align:center
is essential to joy 
and success in Jehovah’s service.

00:07:43.279 --> 00:07:47.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
In contrast, unrealistic expectations

00:07:47.316 --> 00:07:49.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
cause discouragement,

00:07:49.318 --> 00:07:51.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
as Proverbs 13:12 says:

00:07:51.854 --> 00:07:56.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Expectation postponed makes the heart sick,

00:07:56.859 --> 00:08:00.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
but a desire realized is a tree of life.”

00:08:01.430 --> 00:08:04.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
Appropriately, we often use this verse

00:08:04.567 --> 00:08:06.836 line:90% position:50% align:center
when referring to expectations

00:08:06.836 --> 00:08:10.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
that are not achieved 
as quickly as we would like.

00:08:10.740 --> 00:08:15.011 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, expectations that are too high

00:08:15.011 --> 00:08:17.747 line:90% position:50% align:center
can also make our heart sick.

00:08:19.015 --> 00:08:24.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice this quote
from the August 8, 1983, issue of <i> Awake!: </i>

00:08:25.021 --> 00:08:28.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Disappointment is often not so much a matter

00:08:28.491 --> 00:08:31.027 line:90% position:50% align:center
“of ‘expectation postponed,’

00:08:31.027 --> 00:08:33.829 line:90% position:50% align:center
“as expectations too high.

00:08:33.829 --> 00:08:36.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Now at times it is good to have high goals,

00:08:36.699 --> 00:08:38.968 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to ‘aim for the stars.’

00:08:38.968 --> 00:08:41.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
“But <i>always </i> expecting to come out on top

00:08:41.904 --> 00:08:46.142 line:90% position:50% align:center
is a surefire way to beckon disappointment.”

00:08:47.009 --> 00:08:49.312 line:90% position:50% align:center
To avoid disappointment,

00:08:49.312 --> 00:08:53.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
our expectations should be
reasonable and sensible.

00:08:54.617 --> 00:08:56.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
In our discussion,

00:08:56.619 --> 00:09:01.624 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’re going to answer the following
three questions about our expectations:

00:09:02.592 --> 00:09:06.362 line:90% position:50% align:center
(1) Why must we be realistic

00:09:06.362 --> 00:09:09.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
about what we expect from ourselves?

00:09:10.199 --> 00:09:13.336 line:90% position:50% align:center
(2) Why must we be realistic

00:09:13.336 --> 00:09:16.372 line:90% position:50% align:center
in what we expect 
from our brothers and sisters?

00:09:17.473 --> 00:09:21.844 line:90% position:50% align:center
(3) Why is it realistic to expect

00:09:21.844 --> 00:09:26.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah will reward us 
for our faithful sacred service?

00:09:28.384 --> 00:09:30.386 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our first question is,

00:09:30.386 --> 00:09:35.324 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why must we be realistic 
about what we expect from ourselves?

00:09:36.292 --> 00:09:41.297 line:90% position:50% align:center
Of course, we love Jehovah
with our whole heart, mind, and soul,

00:09:41.297 --> 00:09:44.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we want to do everything for his glory.

00:09:45.334 --> 00:09:48.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, the reality is

00:09:48.070 --> 00:09:52.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
that no matter how much we love Jehovah
and want to obey him,

00:09:52.208 --> 00:09:55.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
we are sinful descendants of Adam.

00:09:55.044 --> 00:09:57.046 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a result,

00:09:57.046 --> 00:10:01.651 line:90% position:50% align:center
we occasionally transgress in thought,
word, and deed.

00:10:02.718 --> 00:10:05.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ecclesiastes 7:20 states:

00:10:05.321 --> 00:10:07.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For there is no righteous man on earth

00:10:07.957 --> 00:10:11.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
who always does good and never sins.”

00:10:12.295 --> 00:10:14.297 line:90% position:50% align:center
And James 3:2 reads:

00:10:14.297 --> 00:10:18.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For we all stumble many times.

00:10:18.100 --> 00:10:20.636 line:90% position:50% align:center
“If anyone does not stumble in word,

00:10:20.636 --> 00:10:22.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
he is a perfect man.”

00:10:23.205 --> 00:10:26.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
Perhaps you can relate 
to the feelings of the apostle Paul

00:10:26.475 --> 00:10:30.880 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Romans 7:18-20:

00:10:31.314 --> 00:10:34.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For I know that in me,

00:10:34.150 --> 00:10:36.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that is, in my flesh,

00:10:36.619 --> 00:10:39.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
“there dwells nothing good;

00:10:39.188 --> 00:10:42.658 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for I have the desire to do what is fine

00:10:42.658 --> 00:10:45.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but not the ability to carry it out.

00:10:45.194 --> 00:10:49.298 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For I do not do the good that I wish,

00:10:49.298 --> 00:10:51.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but the bad that I do not wish

00:10:51.901 --> 00:10:54.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
“is what I practice.

00:10:54.003 --> 00:10:57.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
“If, then, I do what I do not wish,

00:10:57.406 --> 00:11:00.543 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I am no longer the one carrying it out,

00:11:00.543 --> 00:11:03.713 line:90% position:50% align:center
but it is the sin dwelling in me.”

00:11:03.713 --> 00:11:08.584 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul’s struggle with his sinful flesh
made him feel miserable.

00:11:09.452 --> 00:11:10.853 line:90% position:50% align:center
At times,

00:11:10.853 --> 00:11:13.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
we too might feel dejected,

00:11:13.689 --> 00:11:18.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
disappointed, 
and frustrated over our shortcomings.

00:11:19.295 --> 00:11:21.964 line:90% position:50% align:center
We may begin to feel like a failure.

00:11:23.499 --> 00:11:27.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
What enabled Paul to continue
serving Jehovah with joy and zeal?

00:11:29.205 --> 00:11:32.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
He honestly acknowledged his sinful condition

00:11:32.308 --> 00:11:36.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
and had complete confidence
in the ransom sacrifice of Jesus Christ.

00:11:37.980 --> 00:11:42.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul went on to say at Romans 7:24, 25:

00:11:42.485 --> 00:11:45.521 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Miserable man that I am!

00:11:45.521 --> 00:11:47.356 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Who will rescue me

00:11:47.356 --> 00:11:50.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
“from the body undergoing this death?

00:11:50.192 --> 00:11:54.230 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thanks to God through Jesus Christ our Lord!”

00:11:54.964 --> 00:11:58.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, through Jehovah’s undeserved kindness

00:11:58.434 --> 00:12:01.170 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his loving provision of the ransom,

00:12:01.170 --> 00:12:04.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can confidently remain in Jehovah’s love

00:12:04.039 --> 00:12:07.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
and render worship that’s acceptable to him,

00:12:07.042 --> 00:12:09.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
even in our imperfect state.

00:12:11.113 --> 00:12:16.118 line:90% position:50% align:center
How powerful is the ransom
in allowing us to have a clean conscience

00:12:16.118 --> 00:12:19.021 line:90% position:50% align:center
and retain Jehovah’s approval?

00:12:19.021 --> 00:12:22.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
Acts 3:19 answers this question:

00:12:23.292 --> 00:12:25.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Repent, therefore,

00:12:25.795 --> 00:12:28.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and turn around so as to get your sins

00:12:28.764 --> 00:12:32.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
“blotted out,
so that seasons of refreshing

00:12:32.301 --> 00:12:34.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
may come from Jehovah himself.”

00:12:34.937 --> 00:12:38.774 line:90% position:50% align:center
The original-language word
translated “blotted out”

00:12:38.774 --> 00:12:42.411 line:90% position:50% align:center
means “to cause to disappear by wiping,”

00:12:42.411 --> 00:12:45.347 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to remove so as to leave no trace.”

00:12:46.449 --> 00:12:49.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah completely wipes out our sin.

00:12:50.986 --> 00:12:52.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
To illustrate:

00:12:52.988 --> 00:12:55.191 line:90% position:50% align:center
Imagine a white writing surface

00:12:55.191 --> 00:12:58.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
representing our clean standing
before Jehovah.

00:12:58.594 --> 00:13:02.231 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now imagine that red dots are drawn on it,

00:13:02.231 --> 00:13:04.600 line:90% position:50% align:center
representing our sins.

00:13:04.600 --> 00:13:08.370 line:90% position:50% align:center
We should not view the ransom
as if Jehovah draws an <i> X</i>

00:13:08.370 --> 00:13:11.507 line:90% position:50% align:center
over each dot to cross them out.

00:13:11.507 --> 00:13:14.610 line:90% position:50% align:center
Those red dots would still be visible.

00:13:14.610 --> 00:13:17.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
Rather, we should imagine Jehovah,

00:13:17.646 --> 00:13:22.051 line:90% position:50% align:center
based on the ransom,
completely erasing the red dots

00:13:22.051 --> 00:13:25.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that a clean, 
white writing surface is restored.

00:13:26.388 --> 00:13:31.393 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah further reassures us 
of the completeness of his forgiveness

00:13:31.393 --> 00:13:36.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the words recorded at Psalm 103:12-14.

00:13:37.600 --> 00:13:41.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah ‘remembers that we are dust’

00:13:41.871 --> 00:13:45.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
and does not expect perfection from us.

00:13:46.675 --> 00:13:49.211 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a merciful Father,

00:13:49.211 --> 00:13:53.883 line:90% position:50% align:center
he puts our sins “as far off 
as the sunrise is from the sunset.”

00:13:55.584 --> 00:13:59.488 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even if a servant of Jehovah 
commits a serious sin,

00:13:59.488 --> 00:14:04.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
if he is truly repentant with godly sadness,

00:14:04.360 --> 00:14:07.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
his sin can be blotted out,

00:14:07.463 --> 00:14:09.798 line:90% position:50% align:center
completely forgiven.

00:14:11.467 --> 00:14:14.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
Therefore, it is essential for us to maintain

00:14:14.637 --> 00:14:17.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
a reasonable, sensible,

00:14:17.806 --> 00:14:20.809 line:90% position:50% align:center
realistic view of our imperfect state.

00:14:22.044 --> 00:14:24.713 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re going to make mistakes,

00:14:24.713 --> 00:14:28.150 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we must have full trust in the reality

00:14:28.150 --> 00:14:31.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Jehovah’s forgiveness based on the ransom.

00:14:32.621 --> 00:14:36.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
Also, we can learn valuable lessons 
from our errors

00:14:36.692 --> 00:14:39.528 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that we’ll be less likely to repeat them.

00:14:41.196 --> 00:14:43.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
We need patience, though,

00:14:43.432 --> 00:14:46.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
because some personality flaws and bad habits

00:14:46.735 --> 00:14:48.804 line:90% position:50% align:center
may not go away overnight.

00:14:49.605 --> 00:14:54.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some of them may even be a lifelong battle.

00:14:55.844 --> 00:14:59.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
At times, we may need counsel and discipline.

00:15:01.150 --> 00:15:04.587 line:90% position:50% align:center
What should we realistically expect
when receiving discipline?

00:15:05.821 --> 00:15:08.424 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hebrews 12:11-13

00:15:08.424 --> 00:15:13.362 line:90% position:50% align:center
makes it clear 
that initially it will not “be joyous.”

00:15:14.129 --> 00:15:16.465 line:90% position:50% align:center
“It is painful”!

00:15:16.465 --> 00:15:20.269 line:90% position:50% align:center
However, when we humbly accept discipline

00:15:20.269 --> 00:15:22.271 line:90% position:50% align:center
and apply the counsel,

00:15:22.271 --> 00:15:25.841 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can be sure that we will gain inner peace

00:15:25.841 --> 00:15:28.410 line:90% position:50% align:center
and be a better servant of Jehovah.

00:15:29.511 --> 00:15:32.948 line:90% position:50% align:center
Therefore, do not give up,

00:15:32.948 --> 00:15:35.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
but keep making progress.

00:15:36.352 --> 00:15:40.789 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never allow the Devil 
to convince you that you are a failure.

00:15:41.991 --> 00:15:45.461 line:90% position:50% align:center
As stated in the September 1, 2001,

00:15:45.461 --> 00:15:48.197 line:90% position:50% align:center
issue of <i> The Watchtower,</i>  on page 18:

00:15:49.431 --> 00:15:54.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Satan would like nothing better 
than to rob you of your peace . . . .

00:15:54.069 --> 00:15:57.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He would surely like you 
to feel that your imperfection

00:15:57.272 --> 00:16:00.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
“makes your service unacceptable to God.

00:16:00.709 --> 00:16:04.713 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never allow the Devil to demoralize you!”

00:16:05.914 --> 00:16:09.418 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our second question for consideration is,

00:16:09.418 --> 00:16:11.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why must we be realistic

00:16:11.620 --> 00:16:14.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
in what we expect
from our brothers and sisters?

00:16:16.191 --> 00:16:20.029 line:90% position:50% align:center
Just as it’s essential
to avoid having expectations

00:16:20.029 --> 00:16:22.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
that are too high for ourselves,

00:16:22.765 --> 00:16:27.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
we must also avoid expecting too much
from our brothers and sisters.

00:16:28.303 --> 00:16:32.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
Such unreasonable expectations create stress,

00:16:32.274 --> 00:16:35.144 line:90% position:50% align:center
disappointment, and frustration.

00:16:36.345 --> 00:16:39.782 line:90% position:50% align:center
The <i> Awake!</i>  of September 8, 1994,

00:16:39.782 --> 00:16:42.518 line:90% position:50% align:center
quoted a factory supervisor who said:

00:16:43.886 --> 00:16:47.389 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You have to accept people as they are.

00:16:47.389 --> 00:16:50.225 line:90% position:50% align:center
“If you expect more than they can give,

00:16:50.225 --> 00:16:52.561 line:90% position:50% align:center
“[you] will elevate the stress level,

00:16:52.561 --> 00:16:55.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
making everyone unhappy.”

00:16:57.900 --> 00:17:00.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
We should expect from our fellow workers

00:17:00.669 --> 00:17:03.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
what Jehovah and Jesus expect from them.

00:17:05.007 --> 00:17:07.643 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus’ illustration of the talents,

00:17:07.643 --> 00:17:11.914 line:90% position:50% align:center
recorded in Matthew chapter 25,
conveys their thinking.

00:17:13.215 --> 00:17:17.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
The main point of this illustration
is that the Master, Jesus,

00:17:17.653 --> 00:17:20.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
expects each of his anointed brothers

00:17:20.889 --> 00:17:25.894 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the slaves and, by extension,
those who are of the other sheep—

00:17:25.894 --> 00:17:28.964 line:90% position:50% align:center
to do his or her best

00:17:28.964 --> 00:17:32.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the assigned work
of preaching the good news.

00:17:33.569 --> 00:17:35.738 line:90% position:50% align:center
How did Jesus distribute the work?

00:17:36.672 --> 00:17:41.043 line:90% position:50% align:center
Matthew 25:15 provides the answer:

00:17:41.777 --> 00:17:45.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He gave five talents to one,

00:17:45.447 --> 00:17:47.449 line:90% position:50% align:center
“two to another,

00:17:47.449 --> 00:17:50.085 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and one to still another,

00:17:50.085 --> 00:17:53.756 line:90% position:50% align:center
“to each according to his own ability,

00:17:53.756 --> 00:17:55.758 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he went abroad.”

00:17:55.758 --> 00:17:59.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah and Jesus are pleased with

00:17:59.328 --> 00:18:01.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
and will reward each of us

00:18:01.797 --> 00:18:06.001 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we do our best
within our circumstances and ability.

00:18:07.236 --> 00:18:10.506 line:90% position:50% align:center
When the slave with two talents 
gained two more,

00:18:10.506 --> 00:18:13.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
the master did not say to him,

00:18:13.008 --> 00:18:17.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Why did you not gain five more 
like your fellow slave?’

00:18:17.379 --> 00:18:21.950 line:90% position:50% align:center
He gave the two-talent slave
the same commendation

00:18:21.950 --> 00:18:26.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
as the one who was given the five
and gained five more:

00:18:26.955 --> 00:18:31.627 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Well done, good and faithful slave!

00:18:31.627 --> 00:18:34.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You were faithful over a few things.

00:18:34.229 --> 00:18:37.332 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I will appoint you over many things.

00:18:37.332 --> 00:18:40.536 line:90% position:50% align:center
Enter into the joy of your master.”

00:18:40.536 --> 00:18:42.671 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a result,

00:18:42.671 --> 00:18:46.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
the two-talent slave
could be just as successful

00:18:46.441 --> 00:18:50.712 line:90% position:50% align:center
and joyful as the five-talent slave.

00:18:50.712 --> 00:18:55.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
They both met
their master’s reasonable expectations,

00:18:55.317 --> 00:18:57.886 line:90% position:50% align:center
and their master was joyful too.

00:18:59.154 --> 00:19:01.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
What a fine lesson for all of us,

00:19:01.924 --> 00:19:04.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
including those serving as elders!

00:19:04.293 --> 00:19:07.963 line:90% position:50% align:center
In imitation of Jehovah and Jesus,

00:19:07.963 --> 00:19:11.233 line:90% position:50% align:center
we should never put pressure on our brothers

00:19:11.233 --> 00:19:13.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
to do more than they’re capable of doing.

00:19:14.603 --> 00:19:18.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
Failure to take this reasonable
and realistic approach

00:19:18.307 --> 00:19:21.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
can result in much frustration.

00:19:23.378 --> 00:19:27.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
Another way that we show 
we have reasonable expectations

00:19:27.583 --> 00:19:30.886 line:90% position:50% align:center
is to acknowledge 
that from time to time disagreements

00:19:30.886 --> 00:19:35.224 line:90% position:50% align:center
and hurt feelings
will arise among our brothers.

00:19:35.224 --> 00:19:37.626 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you ever heard someone say,

00:19:37.626 --> 00:19:42.531 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I expect to be treated that way
by the world, but not by my brother”?

00:19:42.531 --> 00:19:45.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is it reasonable to expect

00:19:45.033 --> 00:19:48.637 line:90% position:50% align:center
that there will not be any 
difficulties among brothers?

00:19:48.637 --> 00:19:50.639 line:90% position:50% align:center
No.

00:19:50.639 --> 00:19:52.708 line:90% position:50% align:center
Does Jesus expect that at times

00:19:52.708 --> 00:19:56.511 line:90% position:50% align:center
his disciples will have difficulties 
among themselves?

00:19:56.511 --> 00:19:58.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes.

00:19:58.513 --> 00:20:00.515 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why can we say this?

00:20:01.650 --> 00:20:03.652 line:90% position:50% align:center
Remember some of the expressions

00:20:03.652 --> 00:20:06.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus used throughout
the Sermon on the Mount:

00:20:07.990 --> 00:20:12.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Happy are the peacemakers, 
since they will be called sons of God.”

00:20:13.929 --> 00:20:16.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
“If . . . you are bringing 
your gift to the altar

00:20:16.899 --> 00:20:21.336 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and there you remember
that your brother has something against you,

00:20:21.336 --> 00:20:25.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
“leave your gift there in front of the altar, 
and go away.

00:20:26.275 --> 00:20:29.745 line:90% position:50% align:center
“First make your peace with your brother,

00:20:29.745 --> 00:20:32.781 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then come back and offer your gift.”

00:20:34.216 --> 00:20:36.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Forgive us our debts,

00:20:36.351 --> 00:20:39.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we also have forgiven our debtors.”

00:20:40.989 --> 00:20:45.093 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Stop judging that you may not be judged.”

00:20:46.295 --> 00:20:49.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
These verses show
that Jesus knew his disciples

00:20:49.998 --> 00:20:52.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
would have challenges among themselves.

00:20:52.901 --> 00:20:55.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was a realistic expectation.

00:20:56.939 --> 00:21:00.242 line:90% position:50% align:center
But it’s also reasonable 
to conclude that these problems

00:21:00.242 --> 00:21:05.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
can be successfully resolved 
if godly principles are applied.

00:21:05.213 --> 00:21:08.517 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then peace can be restored.

00:21:08.517 --> 00:21:11.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
Additionally, we should expect some tensions

00:21:11.653 --> 00:21:14.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
to arise among the brotherhood today.

00:21:14.690 --> 00:21:17.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
But by applying Bible principles,

00:21:17.192 --> 00:21:20.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
peace can be restored and maintained.

00:21:22.531 --> 00:21:24.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll now consider our third question:

00:21:26.034 --> 00:21:29.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why is it realistic to expect
that Jehovah will reward us

00:21:29.771 --> 00:21:31.773 line:90% position:50% align:center
for our faithful sacred service?

00:21:33.008 --> 00:21:35.010 line:90% position:50% align:center
At Hebrews 11:6, 

00:21:35.010 --> 00:21:37.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Bible tells us that Jehovah

00:21:37.045 --> 00:21:40.716 line:90% position:50% align:center
is “the rewarder 
of those earnestly seeking him.”

00:21:41.950 --> 00:21:44.853 line:90% position:50% align:center
And at 1 Corinthians 15:58,

00:21:44.853 --> 00:21:46.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
the apostle Paul encourages us

00:21:46.855 --> 00:21:50.392 line:90% position:50% align:center
to have “plenty to do
in the work of the Lord,

00:21:50.392 --> 00:21:54.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
knowing that your labor is not in vain.”

00:21:55.831 --> 00:21:59.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul was absolutely sure
of his heavenly reward.

00:22:00.402 --> 00:22:03.372 line:90% position:50% align:center
Despite his sins 
prior to becoming a Christian

00:22:03.372 --> 00:22:06.675 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his battles with sinful inclinations,

00:22:06.675 --> 00:22:08.777 line:90% position:50% align:center
please note his confidence

00:22:08.777 --> 00:22:13.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
expressed at 2 Timothy 4:7, 8:

00:22:14.249 --> 00:22:17.486 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I have fought the fine fight,

00:22:17.486 --> 00:22:20.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I have run the race to the finish,

00:22:20.288 --> 00:22:22.758 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I have observed the faith.

00:22:22.758 --> 00:22:24.493 line:90% position:50% align:center
“From this time on,

00:22:24.493 --> 00:22:27.996 line:90% position:50% align:center
“there is reserved for me 
the crown of righteousness,

00:22:27.996 --> 00:22:30.499 line:90% position:50% align:center
“which the Lord, the righteous judge,

00:22:30.499 --> 00:22:33.769 line:90% position:50% align:center
“will give me as a reward in that day,

00:22:33.769 --> 00:22:35.437 line:90% position:50% align:center
“yet not to me only,

00:22:35.437 --> 00:22:39.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
but also to all those
who have loved his manifestation.”

00:22:40.375 --> 00:22:45.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can have similar confidence
in the reward Jehovah has promised,

00:22:45.380 --> 00:22:47.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
whether our hope is heavenly

00:22:47.916 --> 00:22:51.953 line:90% position:50% align:center
or to enjoy everlasting life 
on a paradise earth!

00:22:53.121 --> 00:22:56.258 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is a realistic expectation

00:22:56.258 --> 00:23:00.462 line:90% position:50% align:center
because our reasonable and loving God
has promised it,

00:23:00.462 --> 00:23:02.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he does not lie.

00:23:02.864 --> 00:23:06.001 line:90% position:50% align:center
Therefore, may we develop

00:23:06.001 --> 00:23:10.806 line:90% position:50% align:center
and maintain
realistic expectations for ourselves

00:23:10.806 --> 00:23:13.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
and for our fellow workers.

00:23:13.642 --> 00:23:16.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
May we never lose sight of the reality

00:23:16.678 --> 00:23:20.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah
will reward “those earnestly seeking him.”

00:23:22.217 --> 00:23:24.986 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we have realistic expectations,

00:23:24.986 --> 00:23:29.558 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can find joy and success
in our service to Jehovah now,

00:23:29.558 --> 00:23:34.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
as well as have the prospect
of doing so forever.

00:23:38.600 --> 00:23:42.671 line:90% position:50% align:center
Young ones,
no doubt you have many expectations

00:23:42.671 --> 00:23:46.141 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the life that lies ahead of you.

00:23:46.141 --> 00:23:49.478 line:90% position:50% align:center
Be assured
that Jehovah wants the best for you

00:23:49.478 --> 00:23:53.381 line:90% position:50% align:center
and will give you holy spirit
and the direction you need

00:23:53.381 --> 00:23:55.383 line:90% position:50% align:center
to make good choices.

00:23:56.918 --> 00:23:59.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what can you do if you make a decision

00:23:59.988 --> 00:24:04.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
that in the end
disappoints you or those who love you?

00:24:05.527 --> 00:24:07.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s watch this next episode:

00:24:07.529 --> 00:24:11.766 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>My Teen Life</i>
<i>—How Can I Fix My Mistakes? </i>

00:24:20.342 --> 00:24:23.178 line:10% position:50% align:center
I started to make a lot of friends at school,

00:24:23.178 --> 00:24:26.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
and aside from school,
I began learning how to Rollerblade.

00:24:26.448 --> 00:24:30.252 line:90% position:50% align:center
So whenever I’d go out to practice,
I’d meet lots of different people.

00:24:31.186 --> 00:24:33.188 line:10% position:50% align:center
I made some mistakes

00:24:33.188 --> 00:24:34.923 line:10% position:50% align:center
because of bad associations.

00:24:34.923 --> 00:24:38.760 line:90% position:50% align:center
We started going out at night
and maybe just drinking a little alcohol.

00:24:38.760 --> 00:24:42.230 line:90% position:50% align:center
But eventually, we were drinking a lot.

00:24:42.230 --> 00:24:44.399 line:90% position:50% align:center
By the time I realized what was happening,

00:24:44.399 --> 00:24:46.234 line:90% position:50% align:center
I was already really involved.

00:24:46.234 --> 00:24:48.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
I was 17 years old.

00:24:48.236 --> 00:24:50.238 line:90% position:50% align:center
I started being close friends with them.

00:24:50.238 --> 00:24:52.641 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were everything to me,
and I really trusted them.

00:24:53.742 --> 00:24:55.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were doing some wrong things

00:24:55.744 --> 00:24:58.947 line:90% position:50% align:center
like doing drugs and using bad language.

00:24:58.947 --> 00:25:00.949 line:90% position:50% align:center
But I thought: ‘I’m just with them.

00:25:00.949 --> 00:25:04.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
As long as I don’t do what they’re doing,
it’s not a problem.’

00:25:09.824 --> 00:25:14.129 line:90% position:50% align:center
I began to make excuses,
saying that it didn’t really matter

00:25:14.129 --> 00:25:16.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that there wasn’t anything wrong
with what I was doing.

00:25:16.598 --> 00:25:19.734 line:90% position:50% align:center
My spiritual routine
was just going to the meetings.

00:25:19.734 --> 00:25:22.037 line:90% position:50% align:center
I started missing some meetings.

00:25:22.037 --> 00:25:25.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
I never prayed.
I didn’t even know how to do personal study.

00:25:25.106 --> 00:25:27.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
I wasn’t reading the Bible every day.

00:25:27.442 --> 00:25:29.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this group of friends,

00:25:29.744 --> 00:25:33.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
there was a boy who liked me
and asked me out.

00:25:33.481 --> 00:25:36.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
And since all my friends were dating,
I thought, ‘Why not?’

00:25:36.618 --> 00:25:40.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I started dating him,
and my parents had no idea.

00:25:40.622 --> 00:25:43.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’d lie about where I was going,
what I’d be doing, and who I’d be with.

00:25:43.925 --> 00:25:46.628 line:90% position:50% align:center
I was pretty much
two completely different people.

00:25:46.628 --> 00:25:50.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
At home, I was one way,
and with my friends, I was another.

00:25:50.165 --> 00:25:53.501 line:90% position:50% align:center
I tried to pray to Jehovah,
but I just couldn’t.

00:25:53.501 --> 00:25:56.404 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt ashamed because I knew inside

00:25:56.404 --> 00:25:59.608 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah wasn’t happy
with what I was doing.

00:25:59.608 --> 00:26:02.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
My conscience really bothered me.

00:26:06.548 --> 00:26:08.883 line:90% position:50% align:center
There was a moment when my boyfriend

00:26:08.883 --> 00:26:11.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then some of those friends
really let me down.

00:26:11.753 --> 00:26:16.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
I began thinking about how I
didn’t have anyone else in my life.

00:26:16.591 --> 00:26:19.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
One time, we were all drinking,

00:26:19.194 --> 00:26:22.097 line:90% position:50% align:center
and this girl invited us all
to go to her house.

00:26:22.097 --> 00:26:23.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
I started thinking

00:26:23.898 --> 00:26:27.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
about what might happen
if I said yes to that girl’s invitation.

00:26:28.903 --> 00:26:32.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
I knew that there’d be drinking, drugs,

00:26:32.474 --> 00:26:35.777 line:90% position:50% align:center
and maybe even something immoral
might happen.

00:26:35.777 --> 00:26:38.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
So after having not prayed
for a really long time,

00:26:38.513 --> 00:26:43.518 line:90% position:50% align:center
I closed my eyes and said:
“Jehovah, please help me.

00:26:45.120 --> 00:26:48.790 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m just so alone.
I don’t have anyone.”

00:26:50.125 --> 00:26:53.128 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt completely abandoned by everyone.

00:26:53.628 --> 00:26:57.132 line:90% position:50% align:center
So right then and there,
I said a prayer to Jehovah,

00:26:57.132 --> 00:27:00.168 line:90% position:50% align:center
asking him
that if he would help me to say no,

00:27:00.168 --> 00:27:03.305 line:90% position:50% align:center
from that day forward,
I would stop associating with those friends

00:27:03.305 --> 00:27:05.307 line:90% position:50% align:center
and serve him whole-souled.

00:27:05.307 --> 00:27:08.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many times,
I asked Jehovah to forgive me.

00:27:08.076 --> 00:27:10.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
I said:
“Jehovah, you’re the only one I have.

00:27:11.680 --> 00:27:13.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please help me.”

00:27:13.448 --> 00:27:14.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that’s exactly what happened.

00:27:14.916 --> 00:27:18.987 line:90% position:50% align:center
After saying that prayer,
I felt determined to leave.

00:27:18.987 --> 00:27:21.956 line:90% position:50% align:center
I started thinking
about everything that I’d done

00:27:21.956 --> 00:27:24.926 line:90% position:50% align:center
and how I was putting
not only my own life at risk

00:27:24.926 --> 00:27:27.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
but also my relationship with Jehovah.

00:27:27.762 --> 00:27:30.231 line:90% position:50% align:center
I thought, ‘I’m going to talk to the elders.’

00:27:30.231 --> 00:27:33.001 line:90% position:50% align:center
Since I’m a very shy person,

00:27:33.001 --> 00:27:36.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
the thought of confessing my mistakes
was really difficult.

00:27:36.171 --> 00:27:39.974 line:90% position:50% align:center
I talked to them,
and I told them everything that had happened.

00:27:39.974 --> 00:27:42.844 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was like a weight had been lifted off me.

00:27:44.579 --> 00:27:46.815 line:90% position:50% align:center
I saw that I really wasn’t alone after all.

00:27:46.815 --> 00:27:48.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
I still remember a scripture
that they read to me

00:27:48.850 --> 00:27:51.252 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Psalm 86:5,

00:27:51.252 --> 00:27:53.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
which showed me that Jehovah’s forgiveness

00:27:53.288 --> 00:27:55.790 line:90% position:50% align:center
has no limits if I’m truly repentant.

00:27:55.790 --> 00:27:57.926 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I knew that Jehovah would forgive me.

00:27:57.926 --> 00:28:01.763 line:90% position:50% align:center
But the elders also told me
that I’d have to tell my parents,

00:28:01.763 --> 00:28:03.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
which was very difficult.

00:28:03.998 --> 00:28:07.168 line:90% position:50% align:center
But I thought, ‘Well, I need to speak up.’

00:28:07.168 --> 00:28:11.005 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I just opened up
and told them about what had happened.

00:28:15.343 --> 00:28:17.979 line:90% position:50% align:center
I decided
that I was going talk with an elder,

00:28:17.979 --> 00:28:21.282 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he read a scripture with me
from Philippians 4:7,

00:28:21.282 --> 00:28:23.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
which says that “the peace of God

00:28:23.284 --> 00:28:25.820 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that surpasses all understanding

00:28:25.820 --> 00:28:28.356 line:90% position:50% align:center
will guard [our] hearts.”

00:28:28.356 --> 00:28:32.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I was able to pray again,
knowing that if I really changed,

00:28:32.460 --> 00:28:34.996 line:90% position:50% align:center
I could feel that peace
that comes from Jehovah.

00:28:35.630 --> 00:28:38.633 line:90% position:50% align:center
I started studying the Bible for real.

00:28:38.633 --> 00:28:42.003 line:90% position:50% align:center
I stopped associating with those friends

00:28:42.003 --> 00:28:45.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
and started being more involved
in spiritual things.

00:28:45.106 --> 00:28:48.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had the privilege of getting baptized
and becoming a regular pioneer.

00:28:48.877 --> 00:28:50.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
And today, I’m serving at Bethel.

00:28:50.945 --> 00:28:54.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had the privilege of being invited
to help with construction projects,

00:28:54.416 --> 00:28:56.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
but my greatest privilege

00:28:56.451 --> 00:28:59.621 line:90% position:50% align:center
is the strong friendship
that I have with Jehovah

00:28:59.621 --> 00:29:02.590 line:90% position:50% align:center
and also having true friends.

00:29:02.590 --> 00:29:06.461 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’ve seen that Jehovah
has always been by my side.

00:29:06.461 --> 00:29:08.763 line:90% position:50% align:center
And even when I didn’t want to be with him,

00:29:08.763 --> 00:29:10.765 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah never abandoned me.

00:29:30.418 --> 00:29:33.521 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isn’t it encouraging
to see how Jehovah gives us

00:29:33.521 --> 00:29:37.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
just what we need
to get back up if we stumble?

00:29:38.793 --> 00:29:42.997 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our loving Father
is indeed “ready to forgive.”

00:29:44.199 --> 00:29:46.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our music video this month reminds us

00:29:46.901 --> 00:29:51.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
