00:33:53.614 --> 00:33:58.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
With Jehovah,
that’s always a reasonable expectation.

00:33:59.487 --> 00:34:01.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
More than 20 years ago, 

00:34:01.522 --> 00:34:04.225 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>Awake!</i>  magazine published
the life story

00:34:04.225 --> 00:34:07.228 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Alena Žitníková.

00:34:07.228 --> 00:34:10.231 line:90% position:50% align:center
Alena realized that pleasing Jehovah

00:34:10.231 --> 00:34:13.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
would mean rejection by this world.

00:34:13.534 --> 00:34:17.271 line:90% position:50% align:center
But in the following episode
of <i>Where Are They Now?</i>

00:34:17.271 --> 00:34:21.375 line:90% position:50% align:center
note what she describes
as perhaps an even bigger test.

00:34:24.345 --> 00:34:26.614 line:90% position:50% align:center
My name is Alena Žitníková,

00:34:26.614 --> 00:34:28.883 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I was born into a family

00:34:28.883 --> 00:34:30.985 line:90% position:50% align:center
of a zealous Communist.

00:34:30.985 --> 00:34:34.055 line:90% position:50% align:center
We believed that a world was coming

00:34:34.055 --> 00:34:37.492 line:90% position:50% align:center
where people would have
everything they needed.

00:34:37.492 --> 00:34:41.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
They’d be happy,
and there would be peace worldwide,

00:34:41.529 --> 00:34:43.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I deeply believed it.

00:34:46.400 --> 00:34:49.704 line:90% position:50% align:center
But I found paradise
among God’s people.

00:34:56.978 --> 00:35:01.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
As I grew up,
I realized that Communism

00:35:01.149 --> 00:35:05.987 line:90% position:50% align:center
had its deficits
because I saw its hypocrisy.

00:35:07.321 --> 00:35:10.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
People didn’t practice
what they preached.

00:35:12.193 --> 00:35:14.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
In high school, I met a friend

00:35:14.395 --> 00:35:17.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
who started talking about God and the Bible.

00:35:18.633 --> 00:35:23.404 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the fact that God’s name is Jehovah

00:35:24.572 --> 00:35:27.742 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that something
called God’s Kingdom

00:35:27.742 --> 00:35:30.344 line:90% position:50% align:center
and Armageddon will come

00:35:30.344 --> 00:35:33.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
—those were all new concepts for me.

00:35:35.082 --> 00:35:37.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’d never heard of these things before.

00:35:38.519 --> 00:35:41.189 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’d never even held a Bible in my hand.

00:35:43.624 --> 00:35:46.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
A Bible study
gradually helped me gain faith.

00:35:50.131 --> 00:35:53.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1983, I was baptized in a bathtub.

00:35:53.301 --> 00:35:57.205 line:90% position:50% align:center
At that time, Jehovah’s Witnesses
were under ban.

00:35:58.339 --> 00:36:00.541 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1989,

00:36:00.541 --> 00:36:02.743 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Velvet Revolution took place

00:36:02.743 --> 00:36:04.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Czechoslovakia.

00:36:05.246 --> 00:36:08.282 line:90% position:50% align:center
That also meant a change
for Jehovah’s Witnesses

00:36:10.017 --> 00:36:13.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
because we could begin
to express our faith publicly.

00:36:15.823 --> 00:36:17.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
The house-to-house ministry started,

00:36:17.859 --> 00:36:20.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it was something
amazing and new for me.

00:36:23.130 --> 00:36:26.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
I got to know Petr
in our local congregation,

00:36:26.534 --> 00:36:29.503 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we got married in 1990.

00:36:30.371 --> 00:36:33.107 line:90% position:50% align:center
We entered into full-time service

00:36:33.107 --> 00:36:35.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
two years after the wedding.

00:36:35.576 --> 00:36:39.080 line:90% position:50% align:center
We first started serving as regular pioneers,

00:36:39.080 --> 00:36:40.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
and two years later

00:36:40.514 --> 00:36:43.651 line:90% position:50% align:center
we were invited to Bethel.

00:36:43.651 --> 00:36:47.455 line:90% position:50% align:center
Those were years full of joy

00:36:47.455 --> 00:36:49.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
and full of hard work,

00:36:49.891 --> 00:36:51.893 line:90% position:50% align:center
which greatly enriched me.

00:36:54.061 --> 00:36:56.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
We left Bethel eight years later,

00:36:56.831 --> 00:36:59.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I found that people had changed.

00:37:02.770 --> 00:37:05.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it was a challenge for us

00:37:05.406 --> 00:37:09.443 line:90% position:50% align:center
because now people
had become more materialistic.

00:37:11.479 --> 00:37:13.614 line:90% position:50% align:center
When I learned the truth,

00:37:13.614 --> 00:37:16.284 line:90% position:50% align:center
it seemed to me
that Armageddon was at the door

00:37:16.284 --> 00:37:18.853 line:90% position:50% align:center
—that it would come soon.

00:37:18.853 --> 00:37:21.289 line:90% position:50% align:center
And the world helped us in a way

00:37:21.289 --> 00:37:23.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
because it didn’t want us;

00:37:23.524 --> 00:37:26.327 line:90% position:50% align:center
it didn’t want Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:37:26.327 --> 00:37:30.064 line:90% position:50% align:center
But today’s world, with its freedom,

00:37:30.064 --> 00:37:33.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
doesn’t tell us that it doesn’t want us.

00:37:33.167 --> 00:37:36.237 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, it wants us.

00:37:36.237 --> 00:37:41.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
It wants our time, it wants our attention,

00:37:41.042 --> 00:37:44.912 line:90% position:50% align:center
and therefore
there may be a great danger.

00:37:45.880 --> 00:37:49.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
We could feel
that Armageddon is delaying.

00:37:49.984 --> 00:37:54.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we might feel the need
to fulfill our dreams already today.

00:37:54.255 --> 00:37:59.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah teaches me to be patient.

00:37:59.293 --> 00:38:02.830 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah is a happy God,

00:38:02.830 --> 00:38:07.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
and even when he waits,
he does not wait idly.

00:38:07.068 --> 00:38:11.405 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah is hardworking;
he’s always doing something.

00:38:12.840 --> 00:38:17.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you fill the waiting
with activity, time goes faster.

00:38:18.779 --> 00:38:22.783 line:90% position:50% align:center
The field ministry is very important to me.

00:38:22.783 --> 00:38:25.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sometimes it costs a little effort,

00:38:25.653 --> 00:38:30.191 line:90% position:50% align:center
but my service partners are always
a great encouragement to me.

00:38:30.191 --> 00:38:32.626 line:90% position:50% align:center
With Jehovah’s help,

00:38:32.626 --> 00:38:34.729 line:90% position:50% align:center
we have nice conversations in service.

00:38:34.729 --> 00:38:37.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
And even today, we find people

00:38:37.598 --> 00:38:40.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
who think about the meaning of life.

00:38:41.836 --> 00:38:46.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
Service does not only consist
of house-to-house service;

00:38:46.874 --> 00:38:50.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
service is the whole Christian way of life,

00:38:50.611 --> 00:38:54.348 line:90% position:50% align:center
including caring for brothers and sisters.

00:38:54.348 --> 00:38:58.019 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think serving my brothers and sisters

00:38:58.019 --> 00:39:01.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
requires us to set aside time for them.

00:39:03.024 --> 00:39:07.228 line:90% position:50% align:center
In this way, I can promote
a good atmosphere in the congregation.

00:39:09.030 --> 00:39:13.000 line:90% position:50% align:center
To be in a spiritual paradise,
I must contribute something.

00:39:15.369 --> 00:39:18.139 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a result, the spiritual paradise

00:39:18.139 --> 00:39:22.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
will be bigger, deeper, and more beautiful!

00:39:23.744 --> 00:39:26.881 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we do something for others,

00:39:26.881 --> 00:39:30.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
we don’t think too much
about ourselves—our pain.

00:39:32.887 --> 00:39:37.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think life in Jehovah’s service

00:39:37.925 --> 00:39:40.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
is sometimes challenging,

00:39:43.064 --> 00:39:46.367 line:90% position:50% align:center
but the result is happiness.

00:39:48.002 --> 00:39:50.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
And already today,

00:39:50.538 --> 00:39:55.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
I can say that my dream of a happy life

00:39:55.276 --> 00:39:57.745 line:90% position:50% align:center
has come true.

00:40:10.491 --> 00:40:15.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re encouraged to see
Sister Alena Žitníková and her husband, Petr,

00:40:15.429 --> 00:40:18.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
remain busy in Kingdom service.

00:40:18.599 --> 00:40:20.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
How wonderful that this has helped them

00:40:20.668 --> 00:40:23.838 line:90% position:50% align:center
to have realistic expectations

00:40:23.838 --> 00:40:26.674 line:90% position:50% align:center
and continue to remain joyful!

00:40:27.875 --> 00:40:30.945 line:90% position:50% align:center
In a world that wants our time and energy,

00:40:30.945 --> 00:40:35.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
Alena maintains her focus
by sharing her Christian hope,

00:40:35.316 --> 00:40:37.585 line:90% position:50% align:center
caring for her brothers and sisters,

00:40:37.585 --> 00:40:41.956 line:90% position:50% align:center
and doing her all to encourage others.

00:40:41.956 --> 00:40:44.725 line:90% position:50% align:center
What if you want to encourage others

00:40:44.725 --> 00:40:47.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
but you don’t know what to say?

00:40:47.495 --> 00:40:51.365 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice the lessons we learn
from the apostle Paul’s example

00:40:51.365 --> 00:40:54.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
in this morning worship
presented by Brother David Schafer.

00:40:55.636 --> 00:40:56.637 line:10% position:50% align:center
“If you have

00:40:56.637 --> 00:40:59.773 line:10% position:50% align:center
“any word of encouragement . . . ,

00:40:59.773 --> 00:41:01.142 line:10% position:50% align:center
tell it.”

00:41:01.142 --> 00:41:03.344 line:10% position:50% align:center
Who said those words?

00:41:03.344 --> 00:41:06.080 line:10% position:50% align:center
How or what did the apostle Paul

00:41:06.080 --> 00:41:08.115 line:10% position:50% align:center
say in response?

00:41:08.115 --> 00:41:10.284 line:10% position:50% align:center
How did his audience react?

00:41:10.284 --> 00:41:14.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what can Paul’s example teach us
about encouragement?

00:41:14.955 --> 00:41:17.424 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s open our Bibles to Acts chapter 13.

00:41:17.424 --> 00:41:20.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is the account
of Paul’s first missionary tour.

00:41:20.494 --> 00:41:23.564 line:90% position:50% align:center
After a dangerous journey
of about 110 miles (180 km),

00:41:23.564 --> 00:41:26.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul and his companions
find themselves seated

00:41:26.100 --> 00:41:29.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
in a synagogue in Pisidian Antioch.

00:41:29.670 --> 00:41:32.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 15 says:

00:41:32.406 --> 00:41:35.176 line:90% position:50% align:center
“After the public reading
of the Law and the Prophets,

00:41:35.176 --> 00:41:38.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the presiding officers of the synagogue
sent word to them, saying:

00:41:38.846 --> 00:41:42.716 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Men, brothers, if you have
any word of encouragement for the people,

00:41:42.716 --> 00:41:44.652 line:90% position:50% align:center
tell it.’”

00:41:44.652 --> 00:41:48.889 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, the next five paragraphs
contain Paul’s speech.

00:41:48.889 --> 00:41:50.891 line:90% position:50% align:center
How effective was it?

00:41:50.891 --> 00:41:55.062 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verses 42-44 show the results.

00:41:55.062 --> 00:42:00.034 line:90% position:50% align:center
First, the people begged Paul to come back
and give another talk the next weekend.

00:42:00.034 --> 00:42:04.371 line:90% position:50% align:center
Second, many Jews and proselytes
became believers.

00:42:04.371 --> 00:42:06.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
Third, on the following Sabbath,

00:42:06.574 --> 00:42:10.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
nearly all of the city turned out
to hear Paul’s next talk.

00:42:10.611 --> 00:42:11.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
Impressive.

00:42:11.612 --> 00:42:14.548 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have to ask ourselves,

00:42:14.548 --> 00:42:17.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘What did Paul say in those five paragraphs

00:42:17.251 --> 00:42:20.354 line:90% position:50% align:center
that was so persuasive?’

00:42:20.354 --> 00:42:23.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
One of the first things we note
is his introduction

00:42:23.157 --> 00:42:25.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Acts 13:17:

00:42:25.993 --> 00:42:28.862 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The God of this people Israel chose

00:42:28.862 --> 00:42:31.832 line:90% position:50% align:center
our forefathers.”

00:42:31.832 --> 00:42:34.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, note that inclusive pronoun “our”

00:42:34.735 --> 00:42:38.305 line:90% position:50% align:center
—not your forefathers, not mine—
“our forefathers.”

00:42:38.305 --> 00:42:41.675 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did you realize that the last time
that little word was used in the book of Acts

00:42:41.675 --> 00:42:45.079 line:90% position:50% align:center
was all the way back in chapter 7

00:42:45.079 --> 00:42:48.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
during Stephen’s powerful speech?

00:42:48.082 --> 00:42:51.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
Stephen used the word “our” ten times,

00:42:51.318 --> 00:42:54.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
usually in connection
with the word “forefathers.”

00:42:54.288 --> 00:42:57.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul heard that speech
back when he was Saul of Tarsus.

00:42:57.791 --> 00:43:02.363 line:90% position:50% align:center
And now, more than a decade later,
he himself uses the exact same expression

00:43:02.363 --> 00:43:07.201 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the same purpose
—to establish common ground.

00:43:07.201 --> 00:43:10.004 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Your ancestors are my ancestors.

00:43:10.004 --> 00:43:12.006 line:90% position:50% align:center
I am what you are.’

00:43:12.006 --> 00:43:16.443 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that is the starting point
of true encouragement.

00:43:16.443 --> 00:43:19.046 line:90% position:50% align:center
The <i>Watchtower</i>  article
from which our text is taken

00:43:19.046 --> 00:43:23.517 line:90% position:50% align:center
says that “the Greek word
usually translated ‘encouragement’

00:43:23.517 --> 00:43:27.588 line:90% position:50% align:center
literally means ‘a calling to one’s side.’”

00:43:27.588 --> 00:43:30.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
And, yes, it’s related
to the Greek word for “comfort,”

00:43:30.257 --> 00:43:32.359 line:90% position:50% align:center
which has a similar connotation.

00:43:32.359 --> 00:43:36.697 line:90% position:50% align:center
So Paul began from their perspective:

00:43:36.697 --> 00:43:38.966 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I know where you’re coming from.

00:43:38.966 --> 00:43:41.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
I grew up
learning the same holy writings as you.’

00:43:41.635 --> 00:43:44.104 line:90% position:50% align:center
And then in verses 17-31,

00:43:44.104 --> 00:43:46.974 line:90% position:50% align:center
he uses Jewish history and recent events

00:43:46.974 --> 00:43:49.410 line:90% position:50% align:center
to prove that Jesus was the Messiah.

00:43:49.410 --> 00:43:53.347 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then in verses 32-37, he connects

00:43:53.347 --> 00:43:57.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
current events with fulfilled prophecy

00:43:57.251 --> 00:43:59.386 line:90% position:50% align:center
—prophecy that they knew.

00:43:59.386 --> 00:44:01.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
We do that today, don’t we?

00:44:01.522 --> 00:44:05.893 line:90% position:50% align:center
We go to the door; we read Matthew 24:7;
we ask: “What do you think?

00:44:05.893 --> 00:44:07.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Are the wars, famines, and earthquakes

00:44:07.795 --> 00:44:10.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
“that we’ve seen in recent years
the same as ever

00:44:10.130 --> 00:44:12.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
or are they a distinct fulfillment
of Bible prophecy?”

00:44:12.666 --> 00:44:15.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what is the message?

00:44:15.135 --> 00:44:19.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
That Jehovah is real; that Jehovah is alive;

00:44:19.073 --> 00:44:21.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
his Word is coming true.

00:44:21.208 --> 00:44:24.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
And yet, Paul went further, didn’t he?
He didn’t stop there.

00:44:24.845 --> 00:44:27.014 line:90% position:50% align:center
In verse 33, Paul said:

00:44:27.014 --> 00:44:30.417 line:90% position:50% align:center
“God has completely fulfilled it

00:44:30.417 --> 00:44:32.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
to us.”

00:44:32.419 --> 00:44:34.421 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, this is personal.

00:44:34.421 --> 00:44:37.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah is at work in your life—in my life.

00:44:37.524 --> 00:44:40.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then the big conclusion in verses 38-41.

00:44:40.961 --> 00:44:44.331 line:90% position:50% align:center
In effect, Jehovah did this for you;

00:44:44.331 --> 00:44:47.601 line:90% position:50% align:center
don’t miss out; you can succeed
with Jehovah’s help.

00:44:47.601 --> 00:44:50.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was Paul’s answer to a simple request

00:44:50.771 --> 00:44:54.007 line:90% position:50% align:center
for a “word of encouragement.”

00:44:54.007 --> 00:44:56.310 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s why Paul made disciples.

00:44:56.310 --> 00:44:58.912 line:90% position:50% align:center
And isn’t that how we’re counseled to fulfill

00:44:58.912 --> 00:45:01.048 line:90% position:50% align:center
our student assignments today?

00:45:01.048 --> 00:45:03.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
To strengthen and encourage our audience,

00:45:03.951 --> 00:45:08.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
we should show what Jehovah has done,

00:45:08.088 --> 00:45:11.825 line:90% position:50% align:center
what he is doing, and what he will yet do.

00:45:11.825 --> 00:45:16.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Paul’s speech was so persuasive
that it also drew persecution,

00:45:16.563 --> 00:45:19.299 line:90% position:50% align:center
which followed him to the next two cities.

00:45:19.299 --> 00:45:23.170 line:90% position:50% align:center
In Lystra, his persecutors thought
they had killed him.

00:45:23.170 --> 00:45:27.975 line:90% position:50% align:center
But Acts 14:20, 21 says

00:45:27.975 --> 00:45:30.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
that “on the next day

00:45:30.377 --> 00:45:33.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
“he left with Barnabas for Derbe.

00:45:33.213 --> 00:45:37.451 line:90% position:50% align:center
After declaring the good news to that city
and making quite a few disciples,”

00:45:38.285 --> 00:45:40.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
they faced a choice.

00:45:40.287 --> 00:45:44.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
You can see the choice on Map B13.

00:45:44.691 --> 00:45:46.693 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re looking at the red lines

00:45:46.693 --> 00:45:49.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
indicating Paul’s first missionary tour.

00:45:49.263 --> 00:45:53.534 line:90% position:50% align:center
Derbe is the last stop,
but notice the next town over to the east

00:45:53.534 --> 00:45:55.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Tarsus.

00:45:55.135 --> 00:45:56.537 line:90% position:50% align:center
Sound familiar?

00:45:56.537 --> 00:45:59.006 line:90% position:50% align:center
Saul of Tarsus.

00:45:59.006 --> 00:46:01.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
There was a passageway from Derbe to Tarsus.

00:46:01.642 --> 00:46:03.177 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul would have known the road.

00:46:03.177 --> 00:46:05.312 line:90% position:50% align:center
He used it on his second missionary journey

00:46:05.312 --> 00:46:08.982 line:90% position:50% align:center
and his third missionary journey,
but not this time.

00:46:08.982 --> 00:46:12.986 line:90% position:50% align:center
Acts 14:21
—and the red arrows show that Paul returned

00:46:12.986 --> 00:46:15.756 line:90% position:50% align:center
to all three cities
where he had been persecuted,

00:46:15.756 --> 00:46:18.158 line:90% position:50% align:center
including Pisidian Antioch,

00:46:18.892 --> 00:46:23.230 line:90% position:50% align:center
where he first received the request
for a “word of encouragement.”

00:46:23.230 --> 00:46:25.232 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why? Why return?

00:46:25.232 --> 00:46:28.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
It would have been so easy for him to think:
‘You know, we’ve had a pretty good run here.

00:46:28.502 --> 00:46:30.604 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I helped the ruler of Cyprus into the truth.

00:46:30.604 --> 00:46:33.607 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I performed my first miracle,
striking Elymas blind.

00:46:33.607 --> 00:46:38.579 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘We started new congregations
in Pisidian Antioch, Iconium, Lystra, Derbe.

00:46:38.579 --> 00:46:40.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I endured all manner of hardships.

00:46:40.447 --> 00:46:43.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I was beaten up and stoned
and left for dead.

00:46:43.317 --> 00:46:46.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was a successful missionary tour,
but I need to regroup.’

00:46:46.620 --> 00:46:49.590 line:90% position:50% align:center
No. He didn’t think that way.

00:46:49.590 --> 00:46:51.358 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:46:51.358 --> 00:46:54.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because the needs of the congregation

00:46:54.127 --> 00:46:58.298 line:90% position:50% align:center
outweighed his own personal feelings

00:46:58.298 --> 00:46:59.900 line:90% position:50% align:center
or fears.

00:46:59.900 --> 00:47:04.872 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you suppose that the opposers
who stoned him and left him for dead

00:47:04.872 --> 00:47:09.843 line:90% position:50% align:center
were any kinder
to the new disciples in Lystra?

00:47:09.843 --> 00:47:12.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
Besides, who was taking the lead?

00:47:12.045 --> 00:47:14.314 line:90% position:50% align:center
Paul needed to appoint overseers.

00:47:14.314 --> 00:47:16.750 line:90% position:50% align:center
This was a weighty task.

00:47:16.750 --> 00:47:19.319 line:90% position:50% align:center
So back they went.

00:47:19.319 --> 00:47:23.524 line:90% position:50% align:center
Likewise today, our brothers
are putting the needs of the disciples

00:47:23.524 --> 00:47:26.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
ahead of their own comforts.

00:47:26.293 --> 00:47:27.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you remember these scenes

00:47:27.694 --> 00:47:32.165 line:90% position:50% align:center
from <i>Jehovah’s Witnesses—Faith in Action,</i>
<i>Part 2: Let the Light Shine?</i>

00:47:32.165 --> 00:47:35.102 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, Brother Pillars explains
that when he refused

00:47:35.102 --> 00:47:37.905 line:90% position:50% align:center
to salute the flag in Winnsboro, Texas,

00:47:37.905 --> 00:47:40.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
he was beaten up and hanged.

00:47:40.574 --> 00:47:45.045 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thankfully, the rope broke,
and he survived to tell the story.

00:47:46.146 --> 00:47:49.750 line:90% position:50% align:center
What the video doesn’t tell us
is that Oscar Pillars was a circuit overseer.

00:47:49.750 --> 00:47:53.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some months later,
guess where it was time for him to return?

00:47:53.620 --> 00:47:55.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
Winnsboro, Texas.

00:47:55.622 --> 00:47:58.258 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, in the months
since the hanging incident,

00:47:58.258 --> 00:48:02.162 line:90% position:50% align:center
the brothers hadn’t been preaching downtown
—they were preaching in the rurals.

00:48:02.162 --> 00:48:05.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brother Pillars reasoned
that if he didn’t preach downtown,

00:48:05.632 --> 00:48:09.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
the brothers may never get the courage
to preach there.

00:48:09.670 --> 00:48:12.639 line:90% position:50% align:center
So he checked out all the territories
within the city limits.

00:48:12.639 --> 00:48:17.411 line:90% position:50% align:center
They worked there all morning and had
a beautiful time with no negative incidents,

00:48:17.411 --> 00:48:20.247 line:90% position:50% align:center
except at the very last door.

00:48:20.247 --> 00:48:23.684 line:90% position:50% align:center
A woman said, “Say,

00:48:23.684 --> 00:48:25.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
you’re one of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
aren’t you?”

00:48:25.852 --> 00:48:27.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
He said, “Yes, ma’am, I am.”

00:48:27.921 --> 00:48:31.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
She said, “You know,
we hanged one of you people here,

00:48:31.592 --> 00:48:33.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’ll do it again.”

00:48:33.694 --> 00:48:37.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, he didn’t tell her
that he was the one that they hanged.

00:48:37.698 --> 00:48:42.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what a beautiful example
of standing with your brothers

00:48:42.402 --> 00:48:44.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
and putting their needs

00:48:44.504 --> 00:48:48.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
ahead of your own feelings!

00:48:48.008 --> 00:48:50.177 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we have to say that this Bethel family

00:48:50.177 --> 00:48:52.479 line:90% position:50% align:center
is not self-sparing

00:48:52.479 --> 00:48:55.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
when encouragement is needed.

00:48:55.182 --> 00:48:57.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
At times, though, it could be easy to think,

00:48:57.184 --> 00:49:00.621 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Well, I just don’t know what to say.’

00:49:00.621 --> 00:49:05.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
But is saying something always necessary?

00:49:05.425 --> 00:49:08.729 line:90% position:50% align:center
How do you suppose those in Lystra felt

00:49:08.729 --> 00:49:11.298 line:90% position:50% align:center
just to see Paul again,

00:49:11.298 --> 00:49:14.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
knowing what it must have taken
for him emotionally

00:49:14.801 --> 00:49:16.803 line:90% position:50% align:center
simply to return?

00:49:16.803 --> 00:49:20.574 line:90% position:50% align:center
That of itself spoke volumes.

00:49:20.574 --> 00:49:24.277 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘OK, but I still feel
like I should say something.’

00:49:24.277 --> 00:49:25.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
What did Paul say?

00:49:25.679 --> 00:49:29.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 22: “We must enter
into the Kingdom of God

00:49:29.416 --> 00:49:32.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
through many tribulations.”

00:49:32.052 --> 00:49:35.689 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Kingdom—words of true encouragement

00:49:35.689 --> 00:49:38.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
always center on the Kingdom.

00:49:38.425 --> 00:49:39.893 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re not like Job’s false comforters:

00:49:39.893 --> 00:49:42.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Clearly, you have problems here.
You must be doing something wrong.’

00:49:42.396 --> 00:49:45.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, rather: ‘You’re imitating Jesus.

00:49:45.599 --> 00:49:48.802 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘It brought the wrath of our enemy.
Well done!

00:49:48.802 --> 00:49:53.206 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘And that you’re willing to suffer
proves that this is real.

00:49:53.206 --> 00:49:55.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘You will see Jehovah back you up now.

00:49:55.642 --> 00:49:57.978 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘You will see him reward you in the future.

00:49:57.978 --> 00:50:00.213 line:90% position:50% align:center
Stick with it!’

00:50:00.213 --> 00:50:03.050 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you been called on to offer

00:50:03.050 --> 00:50:05.919 line:90% position:50% align:center
a “word of encouragement”?

00:50:07.020 --> 00:50:09.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t over think it, just go!

00:50:09.923 --> 00:50:14.761 line:90% position:50% align:center
Stand beside those who need you.

00:50:14.761 --> 00:50:16.196 line:90% position:50% align:center
And if you have

00:50:16.196 --> 00:50:20.634 line:90% position:50% align:center
any words of encouragement for the people,
“tell it.”

00:50:21.935 --> 00:50:24.404 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isn’t it faith-strengthening to consider

00:50:24.404 --> 00:50:27.841 line:90% position:50% align:center
both first-century and modern-day examples

00:50:27.841 --> 00:50:31.778 line:90% position:50% align:center
of brothers who poured themselves out
to encourage others,

00:50:31.778 --> 00:50:34.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
even in the face of grave danger?

00:50:37.117 --> 00:50:39.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
Has a health condition caused you to pause

00:50:39.519 --> 00:50:43.957 line:90% position:50% align:center
and reevaluate your goals and expectations?

00:50:43.957 --> 00:50:46.026 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please consider the following interview

00:50:46.026 --> 00:50:49.029 line:90% position:50% align:center
that was presented
to the United States Bethel family.

00:50:50.163 --> 00:50:51.765 line:10% position:50% align:center
Well, we have many fine examples

00:50:51.765 --> 00:50:54.034 line:10% position:50% align:center
of those who have maintained their focus

00:50:54.034 --> 00:50:57.237 line:10% position:50% align:center
during extreme life events.

00:50:57.237 --> 00:51:01.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
Consider the experience
of Felix and Mayra Terrazas

00:51:01.208 --> 00:51:04.077 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the following prerecorded interview.

00:51:05.946 --> 00:51:08.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, it’s a privilege
to be with Felix and Mayra Terrazas,

00:51:08.615 --> 00:51:10.117 line:10% position:50% align:center
serving at Wallkill.

00:51:10.117 --> 00:51:11.284 line:10% position:50% align:center
We understand

00:51:11.284 --> 00:51:13.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s been a very difficult year.

00:51:13.553 --> 00:51:17.057 line:90% position:50% align:center
Could you share some of the details
of your medical condition?

00:51:17.858 --> 00:51:19.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, about a year and a half ago,

00:51:19.259 --> 00:51:20.627 line:10% position:50% align:center
I started developing

00:51:20.627 --> 00:51:23.163 line:10% position:50% align:center
an infrequent pain in my chest,

00:51:23.163 --> 00:51:25.532 line:10% position:50% align:center
which led me to seeing several doctors.

00:51:26.299 --> 00:51:27.768 line:10% position:50% align:center
Soon thereafter,

00:51:27.768 --> 00:51:31.037 line:10% position:50% align:center
I was diagnosed with a malignant tumor

00:51:31.037 --> 00:51:35.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
that was only going to be treatable
by its complete removal.

00:51:35.308 --> 00:51:39.012 line:90% position:50% align:center
After the surgery, we were hoping 
to hear good news moving forward.

00:51:39.813 --> 00:51:42.382 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then, a few weeks later,

00:51:42.382 --> 00:51:46.219 line:90% position:50% align:center
one of my doctors conveyed
to us some of the most difficult words

00:51:46.219 --> 00:51:48.388 line:90% position:50% align:center
that one could imagine hearing

00:51:48.388 --> 00:51:51.892 line:90% position:50% align:center
—a life expectancy of just a few months.

00:51:52.592 --> 00:51:55.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
Wow!
That had to have been difficult to hear.

00:51:55.529 --> 00:51:57.531 line:90% position:50% align:center
How were you able to get your mind
wrapped around that?

00:51:58.565 --> 00:52:03.436 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, as you can imagine, 
after many intense and tearful prayers

00:52:03.436 --> 00:52:06.173 line:90% position:50% align:center
asking Jehovah to give us peace of mind

00:52:06.173 --> 00:52:11.178 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to give us a calm heart and wisdom
to make a good decision,

00:52:11.178 --> 00:52:15.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
we decided on a treatment of hospice care

00:52:15.215 --> 00:52:19.085 line:90% position:50% align:center
that would allow me
to make the most of the time that I had left

00:52:19.085 --> 00:52:23.089 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to be able to give
my very best to Jehovah.

00:52:24.291 --> 00:52:26.226 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s remarkable, Felix.

00:52:26.226 --> 00:52:29.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
And, Mayra, you’re such a supportive wife.

00:52:29.095 --> 00:52:31.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
How have you been able to be so positive?

00:52:31.998 --> 00:52:35.001 line:90% position:50% align:center
I have to say that it is my hope in Jehovah.

00:52:35.001 --> 00:52:37.237 line:90% position:50% align:center
That is what has helped me.

00:52:37.237 --> 00:52:39.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
At the moment,
we are ‘sharing in the sufferings’

00:52:39.739 --> 00:52:41.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
mentioned at 2 Corinthians 1:7.

00:52:42.609 --> 00:52:46.413 line:90% position:50% align:center
But the verse concludes 
that ‘we will also share in the comfort,’

00:52:46.413 --> 00:52:49.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we are also experiencing that right now.

00:52:50.417 --> 00:52:53.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
I have no doubt that I’ll see Felix again
in the resurrection.

00:52:53.854 --> 00:52:55.288 line:90% position:50% align:center
When I look to the future,

00:52:55.288 --> 00:52:58.892 line:90% position:50% align:center
I can vividly picture
us walking through the Paradise earth,

00:52:58.892 --> 00:53:01.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
enjoying Jehovah’s beautiful creation.

00:53:01.795 --> 00:53:05.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is the life, “the real life,” 
that Jehovah promises.

00:53:05.565 --> 00:53:09.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it’s this hope
that gives me joy and peace.

00:53:10.036 --> 00:53:11.171 line:90% position:50% align:center
Beautifully expressed.

00:53:11.171 --> 00:53:12.172 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:53:12.172 --> 00:53:15.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
And, Felix, how have you
been able to be so joyful?

00:53:16.843 --> 00:53:21.848 line:90% position:50% align:center
My relationship with Jehovah
has never been stronger than it is right now.

00:53:21.848 --> 00:53:26.586 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I believe that it’s this closeness
and this intimacy with him

00:53:26.586 --> 00:53:30.457 line:90% position:50% align:center
that is providing me
the joy that I’m experiencing.

00:53:30.457 --> 00:53:33.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, Philippians 4:6, 7

00:53:33.426 --> 00:53:37.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
assures me that “by prayer
and [by] supplication,”

00:53:37.464 --> 00:53:41.701 line:90% position:50% align:center
it says that “the peace of God . . .
will guard your hearts.”

00:53:41.701 --> 00:53:44.104 line:90% position:50% align:center
Prayer has been so indispensable

00:53:44.104 --> 00:53:46.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
in bringing me peace during this process,

00:53:46.840 --> 00:53:50.577 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it’s also amplified my appreciation
for the resurrection

00:53:50.577 --> 00:53:53.713 line:90% position:50% align:center
like I’ve never experienced before.

00:53:53.713 --> 00:53:56.016 line:90% position:50% align:center
Proverbs 12:25, I think,

00:53:56.016 --> 00:53:59.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
perfectly illustrates our current situation.

00:53:59.686 --> 00:54:04.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
There it says:
“Anxiety in a man’s heart weighs it down,

00:54:04.691 --> 00:54:08.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
but a good word
[it says that it] cheers it up.”

00:54:09.262 --> 00:54:12.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
Both Mayra and I have benefited

00:54:12.666 --> 00:54:15.969 line:90% position:50% align:center
from what we feel is an enormous storehouse

00:54:15.969 --> 00:54:19.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
of good words received in the way of concern,

00:54:19.539 --> 00:54:22.309 line:90% position:50% align:center
of love and compassion, from the brotherhood.

00:54:22.309 --> 00:54:26.012 line:90% position:50% align:center
And last, my current circumstances

00:54:26.012 --> 00:54:29.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
have opened up such a wonderful opportunity

00:54:29.316 --> 00:54:32.118 line:90% position:50% align:center
to share Kingdom truths with family members,

00:54:32.118 --> 00:54:36.456 line:90% position:50% align:center
including the beautiful privilege
of being able to study the Bible

00:54:36.456 --> 00:54:39.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
with my mother during the past few months.

00:54:39.726 --> 00:54:41.461 line:90% position:50% align:center
Wow! Amazing!

00:54:41.461 --> 00:54:44.064 line:90% position:50% align:center
Tell us, how has this experience

00:54:44.064 --> 00:54:46.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
affected your faith and trust in Jehovah?

00:54:47.567 --> 00:54:50.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, we have seen Jehovah’s hand
from the very beginning,

00:54:50.403 --> 00:54:53.273 line:90% position:50% align:center
but one time sticks out in my mind.

00:54:53.273 --> 00:54:56.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was the day we received Felix’s prognosis.

00:54:56.977 --> 00:54:59.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
That evening,
the Bethel family <i>Watchtower</i>  Study

00:54:59.679 --> 00:55:03.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
considered the article
“Keep Calm and Trust in Jehovah,”

00:55:03.984 --> 00:55:06.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
and this was followed by a lecture

00:55:06.286 --> 00:55:10.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
entitled “Remain
in Jehovah’s Everlasting Arms.”

00:55:10.690 --> 00:55:14.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah provided us
exactly what we needed to hear

00:55:14.361 --> 00:55:16.496 line:90% position:50% align:center
that very day.

00:55:16.496 --> 00:55:19.632 line:90% position:50% align:center
We felt it was an answer to our prayers,

00:55:19.632 --> 00:55:23.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
as if to reassure us
that he has everything under control.

00:55:23.803 --> 00:55:26.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
This has strengthened my faith
in that Jehovah will continue

00:55:26.539 --> 00:55:31.177 line:90% position:50% align:center
to “more than superabundantly”
provide for us care and guidance

00:55:31.177 --> 00:55:33.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we face new challenges

00:55:33.513 --> 00:55:37.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
and will without a doubt
fulfill his promises for the future.

00:55:39.219 --> 00:55:43.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
I think when you come to understand
that you only have a short time to live,

00:55:43.990 --> 00:55:48.862 line:90% position:50% align:center
you know, that’s something that can
very easily knock you right off of your feet.

00:55:48.862 --> 00:55:51.965 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we know that we have been grasped

00:55:51.965 --> 00:55:54.501 line:90% position:50% align:center
by Jehovah’s caring hands right now,

00:55:54.501 --> 00:55:58.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that is what’s stabilized us.

00:55:58.505 --> 00:56:02.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know, throughout this ordeal,
we have seen Jehovah’s love

00:56:02.042 --> 00:56:04.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
—his care and assistance—

00:56:04.044 --> 00:56:07.981 line:90% position:50% align:center
in every decision, in every step,
that we’ve taken.

00:56:07.981 --> 00:56:11.651 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the first visits to the doctors,
through surgery,

00:56:11.651 --> 00:56:14.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
and into the most difficult part
of the prognosis,

00:56:14.487 --> 00:56:17.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
we have lacked nothing.

00:56:17.157 --> 00:56:20.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
I absolutely know that my faith

00:56:20.326 --> 00:56:24.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
has only been strengthened
by the challenges of this trial.

00:56:25.398 --> 00:56:28.535 line:90% position:50% align:center
So now as I prepare to close my eyes

00:56:28.535 --> 00:56:32.038 line:90% position:50% align:center
and fall asleep for just a brief time,

00:56:32.038 --> 00:56:35.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
it is a privilege for me
to demonstrate to Jehovah my trust

00:56:35.942 --> 00:56:38.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
in all of his promises

00:56:38.278 --> 00:56:42.982 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to maintain complete integrity
right down to the end.

00:56:44.551 --> 00:56:46.719 line:90% position:50% align:center
What an outstanding expression of faith!

00:56:46.719 --> 00:56:48.855 line:90% position:50% align:center
Thank you both so much for sharing

00:56:48.855 --> 00:56:52.926 line:90% position:50% align:center
those deeply personal
and motivating expressions.

00:56:52.926 --> 00:56:55.695 line:90% position:50% align:center
You are a living example of faith in action,

00:56:56.763 --> 00:56:58.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we love you.

00:56:59.365 --> 00:57:01.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
I can’t tell you
how many times I’ve seen that,

00:57:01.868 --> 00:57:03.903 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it’s so moving each time.

00:57:04.604 --> 00:57:06.873 line:90% position:50% align:center
On June 8, 2021,

00:57:06.873 --> 00:57:09.275 line:90% position:50% align:center
our dear brother Felix
went to sleep in death,

00:57:09.275 --> 00:57:12.545 line:90% position:50% align:center
just seven weeks after this interview. 

00:57:12.545 --> 00:57:16.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
And any, frankly, that were
around the Terrazas during this time

00:57:16.082 --> 00:57:18.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
would see firsthand

00:57:18.251 --> 00:57:20.920 line:90% position:50% align:center
the power of faith

00:57:20.920 --> 00:57:25.225 line:90% position:50% align:center
and their focus on wanting to give
Jehovah their absolute best.

00:57:25.225 --> 00:57:26.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was tremendous!

00:57:26.726 --> 00:57:29.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
Mayra, dear Mayra, continues to show

00:57:29.329 --> 00:57:32.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
that same faith and endurance even now.

00:57:32.198 --> 00:57:33.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
And Felix’s mother

00:57:33.967 --> 00:57:37.203 line:90% position:50% align:center
—she has continued to progress spiritually,
we understand.

00:57:37.203 --> 00:57:39.272 line:90% position:50% align:center
Felix will be so happy to hear that.

00:57:40.573 --> 00:57:42.575 line:90% position:50% align:center
For me personally,

00:57:42.575 --> 00:57:47.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
it’s been heartwarming
to see Mayra’s unshakable faith

00:57:47.514 --> 00:57:51.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the love and support
she receives from the Bethel family.

00:57:52.785 --> 00:57:57.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
Along with Mayra,
we long to see Felix again.

00:57:57.690 --> 00:57:59.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even in failing health,

00:57:59.759 --> 00:58:04.164 line:90% position:50% align:center
he used the strength he had
to build up those around him.

00:58:05.064 --> 00:58:07.934 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah truly appreciates shepherds

00:58:07.934 --> 00:58:10.937 line:90% position:50% align:center
with this same self-sacrificing spirit.

00:58:12.839 --> 00:58:16.476 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did you once serve as a congregation elder?

00:58:16.476 --> 00:58:19.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can you serve again?

00:58:19.112 --> 00:58:21.648 line:90% position:50% align:center
Note the ways Jehovah assisted two brothers

00:58:21.648 --> 00:58:24.984 line:90% position:50% align:center
to overcome their feelings of disappointment

00:58:24.984 --> 00:58:28.555 line:90% position:50% align:center
and qualify again to serve their brothers.

00:58:29.889 --> 00:58:33.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
I served as an elder until the end of 2014.

00:58:35.595 --> 00:58:39.265 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that’s when some problems came up,
and I ended up being disqualified.

00:58:42.402 --> 00:58:45.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had already been serving as an elder
for nearly two years.

00:58:45.939 --> 00:58:47.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
But at the time,

00:58:47.106 --> 00:58:49.642 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt that the best thing to do

00:58:49.642 --> 00:58:53.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
would be to stop
and give up my privilege of service

00:58:53.112 --> 00:58:55.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that I could care for myself emotionally.

00:58:58.885 --> 00:59:02.155 line:90% position:50% align:center
Before I lost my privileges,
my qualifications were reviewed by the elders

00:59:02.155 --> 00:59:04.324 line:90% position:50% align:center
on three separate occasions,

00:59:06.659 --> 00:59:08.795 line:10% position:50% align:center
and that ended up dampening my desire

00:59:08.795 --> 00:59:10.797 line:10% position:50% align:center
to want to serve again in the future.

00:59:11.598 --> 00:59:12.932 line:90% position:50% align:center
I began thinking:

00:59:12.932 --> 00:59:15.602 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘A publisher receives
the same reward as an elder.

00:59:15.602 --> 00:59:19.239 line:90% position:50% align:center
So why should I put myself
through that all over again?’

00:59:20.273 --> 00:59:22.775 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you resign or are disqualified

00:59:22.775 --> 00:59:24.544 line:90% position:50% align:center
from serving as an elder,

00:59:25.745 --> 00:59:27.146 line:10% position:50% align:center
you’re not immune

00:59:27.146 --> 00:59:30.116 line:10% position:50% align:center
to feeling like you’re a failure,

00:59:30.116 --> 00:59:31.851 line:10% position:50% align:center
feeling sad,

00:59:31.851 --> 00:59:36.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
and especially feeling
that you’ve let Jehovah down.

00:59:36.656 --> 00:59:39.592 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it’s a fight to remain active.

00:59:40.627 --> 00:59:45.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
One of the biggest things that helped me
during that phase was my wife’s support.

00:59:47.200 --> 00:59:50.169 line:90% position:50% align:center
She believed in me and helped motivate me.

00:59:50.169 --> 00:59:52.505 line:90% position:50% align:center
My wife was already a pioneer,

00:59:52.505 --> 00:59:54.807 line:90% position:50% align:center
and she encouraged me
to start pioneering too.

00:59:54.807 --> 00:59:56.843 line:90% position:50% align:center
So within just a few months,

00:59:56.843 --> 00:59:58.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had already started serving as a pioneer.

00:59:59.912 --> 01:00:03.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was in the ministry
that I began to cultivate a desire

01:00:03.349 --> 01:00:05.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
to serve once again as an elder.

01:00:06.819 --> 01:00:10.156 line:90% position:50% align:center
Getting involved
in activities with the congregation,

01:00:10.156 --> 01:00:12.158 line:90% position:50% align:center
helping out with the cleaning . . .

01:00:14.160 --> 01:00:17.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
Being with my wife in the preaching work,

01:00:18.665 --> 01:00:20.700 line:90% position:50% align:center
conducting Bible studies . . .

01:00:22.368 --> 01:00:24.671 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had a lot of help from the brothers

01:00:24.671 --> 01:00:28.608 line:90% position:50% align:center
who cried with me when I needed to cry

01:00:29.575 --> 01:00:33.346 line:90% position:50% align:center
and who laughed with me
when it was possible to laugh.

01:00:33.346 --> 01:00:35.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
A mature elder helped me to see

01:00:35.581 --> 01:00:38.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
that I needed to leave the matter
in Jehovah’s hands.

01:00:38.885 --> 01:00:42.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
That time period
when I stopped serving as an elder,

01:00:42.121 --> 01:00:46.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
I can say that that may have been
when I prayed the most in all my life.

01:00:46.993 --> 01:00:49.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
I still wasn’t an elder, but I felt at peace.

01:00:50.330 --> 01:00:52.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
I remembered 1 John 3:20,

01:00:52.432 --> 01:00:54.867 line:90% position:50% align:center
that “[Jehovah] is greater than our hearts”

01:00:54.867 --> 01:00:57.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that he knew what I was going through.

01:00:59.005 --> 01:01:02.308 line:90% position:50% align:center
And just because
I wasn’t serving any longer as an elder,

01:01:02.308 --> 01:01:04.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
that didn’t make Jehovah love me any less.

01:01:04.977 --> 01:01:06.379 line:90% position:50% align:center
That helped me a lot.

01:01:07.447 --> 01:01:09.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
The most difficult thing to overcome

01:01:09.549 --> 01:01:12.318 line:90% position:50% align:center
was really the resentment
that I felt toward some brothers

01:01:12.318 --> 01:01:14.787 line:90% position:50% align:center
who had participated in the whole process.

01:01:16.122 --> 01:01:19.258 line:90% position:50% align:center
The scripture at Psalm 119:165

01:01:19.258 --> 01:01:22.528 line:90% position:50% align:center
helped me to see that when you’re going
through a difficult situation,

01:01:22.528 --> 01:01:25.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s the time that you need to show
that you love Jehovah.

01:01:27.433 --> 01:01:30.770 line:90% position:50% align:center
I could see that during that time of my life,

01:01:30.770 --> 01:01:33.740 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s when I had to show
that I really loved Jehovah.

01:01:33.740 --> 01:01:37.643 line:90% position:50% align:center
I would pray to Jehovah each and every day,

01:01:37.643 --> 01:01:40.313 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I would mention those brothers by name.

01:01:40.313 --> 01:01:42.982 line:90% position:50% align:center
That helped me to start softening my heart,

01:01:42.982 --> 01:01:45.985 line:90% position:50% align:center
to lessen and eventually
to eliminate this resentment.

01:01:48.254 --> 01:01:50.289 line:90% position:50% align:center
Trusting in Jehovah

01:01:54.260 --> 01:01:56.629 line:90% position:50% align:center
was so worth it,

01:01:56.629 --> 01:02:00.333 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I felt like it was
a great act of love on his part

01:02:01.868 --> 01:02:05.138 line:90% position:50% align:center
to allow me once again to serve as an elder.

01:02:05.138 --> 01:02:06.472 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it’s as if he told me,

01:02:06.472 --> 01:02:10.243 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Marcelo, I trust that you are going
to do a good job as an elder.’

01:02:11.611 --> 01:02:13.713 line:90% position:50% align:center
We just have to trust in Jehovah.

01:02:13.713 --> 01:02:15.948 line:90% position:50% align:center
When I began to show more trust,

01:02:15.948 --> 01:02:19.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s when things started happening
in a way that I couldn’t have imagined.

01:02:19.552 --> 01:02:21.354 line:90% position:50% align:center
In less than two years,

01:02:21.354 --> 01:02:23.756 line:90% position:50% align:center
I had already begun serving
as an elder again.

01:02:24.557 --> 01:02:27.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in 2016, we received
an invitation to serve at Bethel.

01:02:33.866 --> 01:02:36.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
My wife and I
have now been serving here at Bethel

01:02:36.302 --> 01:02:38.438 line:90% position:50% align:center
for a little more than ten years.

01:02:39.972 --> 01:02:41.974 line:90% position:50% align:center
When you accept the discipline,

01:02:41.974 --> 01:02:45.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
then you stop thinking about privileges

01:02:45.111 --> 01:02:48.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
and start thinking more about the brothers

01:02:48.114 --> 01:02:50.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
and about being more involved
in the ministry.

01:02:51.284 --> 01:02:54.053 line:90% position:50% align:center
I still had the most important privilege:

01:02:55.555 --> 01:02:58.291 line:90% position:50% align:center
that of being one of Jehovah’s Witnesses.

01:03:01.861 --> 01:03:04.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today we learned how important it is

01:03:04.464 --> 01:03:08.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
to have
realistic and reasonable expectations,

01:03:08.100 --> 01:03:11.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
both of ourselves
and of our brothers and sisters.

01:03:12.572 --> 01:03:15.575 line:90% position:50% align:center
Instead of being discouraged
with what we cannot do,

01:03:16.609 --> 01:03:21.180 line:90% position:50% align:center
we rely on Jehovah
and set goals according to what we can do.

01:03:21.180 --> 01:03:25.518 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>My Teen Life</i>
and our music video reminded us

01:03:25.518 --> 01:03:27.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah will give us the help we need

01:03:27.653 --> 01:03:31.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
to get back up
if we suffer a spiritual setback.

01:03:32.792 --> 01:03:34.794 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in <i>Where Are They Now? </i>

01:03:34.794 --> 01:03:37.697 line:90% position:50% align:center
we caught up with Sister Alena Žitníková,

01:03:37.697 --> 01:03:40.833 line:90% position:50% align:center
who reminded us
that serving our brothers and sisters

01:03:40.833 --> 01:03:44.203 line:90% position:50% align:center
can keep us focused and joyful.

01:03:46.105 --> 01:03:49.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
We end this month’s program
with our video postcard

01:03:49.008 --> 01:03:52.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
from our brothers and sisters in Costa Rica.

01:03:52.245 --> 01:03:55.214 line:90% position:50% align:center
Costa Rica is a sparkling gem

01:03:55.214 --> 01:03:57.717 line:90% position:50% align:center
that sits on the so-called Ring of Fire,

01:03:57.717 --> 01:04:00.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
a chain approximately 40,000 kilometers,

01:04:00.686 --> 01:04:02.822 line:90% position:50% align:center
or 25,000 miles, long

01:04:02.822 --> 01:04:07.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
that contains about three quarters
of the earth’s volcanoes.

01:04:07.460 --> 01:04:10.196 line:90% position:50% align:center
Costa Rica has 61 volcanoes

01:04:10.196 --> 01:04:12.198 line:90% position:50% align:center
—and 6 active ones.

01:04:13.099 --> 01:04:15.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
The weather and mountainous countryside

01:04:15.101 --> 01:04:18.538 line:90% position:50% align:center
are ideal for growing delicious coffee.

01:04:20.339 --> 01:04:24.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
The name Costa Rica
means “Rich Coast” in Spanish.

01:04:25.511 --> 01:04:30.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is just a small sampling
of the different animal species here.

01:04:31.083 --> 01:04:33.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
And some are found nowhere else on earth.

01:04:34.854 --> 01:04:38.958 line:90% position:50% align:center
But this country
of more than 5,000,000 inhabitants

01:04:38.958 --> 01:04:43.763 line:90% position:50% align:center
boasts other riches
that are truly precious to Jehovah.

01:04:44.730 --> 01:04:49.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
Over 32,000 publishers of the good news
live in Costa Rica,

01:04:49.502 --> 01:04:53.339 line:90% position:50% align:center
and around 4,000 serve as regular pioneers.

01:04:54.240 --> 01:04:58.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
Their territory is vast and diverse.

01:04:58.377 --> 01:05:01.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even though Spanish is the official language,

01:05:01.380 --> 01:05:04.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
there are groups and congregations
in ten languages.

01:05:04.784 --> 01:05:07.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s go to the city of Limón,

01:05:07.186 --> 01:05:10.389 line:90% position:50% align:center
established near where
Christopher Columbus arrived

01:05:10.389 --> 01:05:12.391 line:90% position:50% align:center
around 1502.

01:05:12.391 --> 01:05:15.962 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here we find a Creole-language congregation
in Costa Rica.

01:05:15.962 --> 01:05:19.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our brothers here
love to participate in the ministry.

01:05:20.499 --> 01:05:24.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example,
they do phone and letter witnessing,

01:05:24.136 --> 01:05:28.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
and they conduct
around 65 Bible studies each month.

01:05:28.040 --> 01:05:32.545 line:90% position:50% align:center
Creole-speaking people
have profound respect for God’s Word

01:05:32.545 --> 01:05:35.414 line:90% position:50% align:center
and love to learn about Jehovah.

01:05:35.414 --> 01:05:37.817 line:90% position:50% align:center
The publishers make good use
of the publications

01:05:37.817 --> 01:05:41.854 line:90% position:50% align:center
and videos available
in the Belize Kriol language.

01:05:41.854 --> 01:05:43.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
Several of these brothers have helped

01:05:43.856 --> 01:05:47.994 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the translation
and audio recording of the Bible

01:05:47.994 --> 01:05:52.698 line:90% position:50% align:center
and other publications,
videos, and songs in Belize Kriol.

01:05:52.698 --> 01:05:56.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our dear brothers and sisters
from Limón, Costa Rica,

01:05:56.402 --> 01:06:00.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
send their love and greetings
to the worldwide brotherhood!

01:06:00.840 --> 01:06:04.110 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we send all of you our love as well.

01:06:04.110 --> 01:06:07.480 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:06:07.480 --> 01:06:09.982 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting!

